    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to provide linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec limited-slip differential, ensuring tactile engagement and superior corner-exit traction. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement to ensure structural and internal longevity. While the exterior shows minor road-wear, the suspension kinematics remain sharp, and the chassis rigidity is uncompromised. This is a purist-spec driver\u2019s car optimized for performance over concours aesthetics.",
